@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "FAQ";
}

<div class="faq-page">
    <h1 class="page-header">FAQ</h1>

    <div class="faq-section">
        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>1. How can I join the Volunteer Fire Department?</h2>
            <p>You can join by visiting our "Join" page, filling out the application form, and submitting the required documents. Our team will contact you for the next steps.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>2. What are the requirements to become a volunteer firefighter?</h2>
            <p>Volunteers must be at least 18 years old, physically fit, and willing to commit to training and emergency response duties. No prior experience is necessary; training is provided.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>3. How can I schedule a fire safety inspection?</h2>
            <p>You can schedule an inspection by calling our office or submitting a request through the "Contact Us" page on our website.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>4. Are donations to the Volunteer Fire Department tax-deductible?</h2>
            <p>Yes, donations are tax-deductible. We are a registered non-profit organization. A receipt will be provided for all donations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>5. What should I do in case of a fire emergency?</h2>
            <p>If you experience a fire emergency, call 911 immediately. Do not attempt to extinguish large fires yourself. Evacuate the area and wait for professional help.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <h2>6. How can I schedule a fire safety presentation for my school or organization?</h2>
            <p>To schedule a presentation, please use the "Contact Us" page or call our office directly. We are happy to educate the community on fire safety.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
